Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Application/Agentic AI Engineer role with NextGen Federal Systems. I bring over three years of professional experience in software engineering, RAG, AI agents, API integration, and cloud-native delivery, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my current Software Engineer role at Sperse, I have built production agentic AI systems that align closely with ReadiChat's focus on specialized agents, workflow orchestration, guardrails, testing frameworks, and enterprise controls. I designed an agentic AI CRM system for AI/ML integration using LangGraph, LangChain, and FastAPI, routing tenant-scoped requests through a workflow orchestration agent to 40+ specialized AI agents and workflow specialists. I also defined reusable agent patterns and agent definitions and configurations, including objectives, behavioral instructions, input/output contracts, safety policies, and tool rules, while refactoring 500+ operations into typed dispatchers that replaced 60+ REST tools and improved tool selection accuracy by 90%. That work gives me direct preparation to translate mission workflows and operational requirements into reliable intelligent agents, tools, validation frameworks, and scalable architectures.

